Him neither story of gods nor thunder- bolts nor heaven with threatening roar could quell, but only stirred up the more the eager courage of his soul, filling him with desire to be the first to burst the fast bars of nature’s portals. Therefore the living force of his soul gained the day: on he passed far beyond the flaming walls of the world and traversed throughout in mind and spirit the immeasurable universe 3 whence he returns a conqueror to tell us what can, what cannot come into being 3 in short on what principle each thing has its powers defined, its deepset boundary mark. Therefore religion is put under foot and trampled upon in turn ,⁰ us 1113 victory brings level with heaven. ’
